data.name: label2.Text
data.value: A database containing audit data for this SQL Server instance already exists. However, the database schema is not supported by this version of SQL Compliance Manager. To avoid losing any previously collected audit data, back up the existing database before you register this instance.

data.name: label25.Text
data.value: A SQLcompliance Agent must be deployed to the computer hosting each audited SQL Server. Auditing cannot be enabled until the agent has been deployed. Select the deployment option to use for this agent:

data.name: radioButtonDeployManually.Text
data.value: &Manually Deploy - Indicates that you will manually install the agent at the physical computer that hosts the SQL Server instance. Note that this option is required for virtual SQL Servers and SQL Servers located across a domain trust boundary.

data.name: label34.Text
data.value: The selected SQL Server instance cannot be configured for auditing. The SQL Server version hosting the SQL Compliance Manager Repository must be greater than or equal to the version of the selected SQL Server instance. For example, to audit a SQL Server 2012 instance, the repository must be hosted on at least a SQL Server 2012 instance.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: Note: The login specified for the SQLcompliance Agent service account needs to be a valid domain account with appropriate permissions for creating traces and stored procedures on the registered SQL Server.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value: The SQLcompliance Agent temporarily stores collected audit data in a trace directory on the computer that hosts the SQL Server instance. Specify whether you want to use the default trace directory path or specify a different path.

data.name: label8.Text
data.value: A connection to the new SQL Server is required before deployment of the SQLcompliance Agent can continue. Make sure that the SQL Server is up and reachable . If you cannot connect to the SQL Server from the Management Console, you will need to manually deploy the SQLcompliance Agent.

data.name: radioCustom.Text
data.value: Custom - Allows you to specify specific audit settings. This collection level is recommended for advanced users only. Before selecting specific audit settings, review the events gathered by the Custom collection level and review the help to better understand your choices.

data.name: label14.Text
data.value: Note: Adding privileged users can only be done if you have permission to list server roles and logins. If the SQL Server is in a non-trusted domain, you will not be able to add privileged users until the SQLcompliance agent is deployed and the server registration is complete.

data.name: label15.Text
data.value: Note: Adding trusted users during server registration can only be done if you have permission to list server roles and logins. If the SQL Server is in a non-trusted domain, you will not be able to add trusted users until the SQLcompliance agent is deployed and the server registration is complete.

data.name: labelNote.Text
data.value: Note: If you are saving audit settings for an AlwaysOn or Clustered nodes, please note anytime you made changes to the nodes including audit settings, corresponding changes should be made to all related nodes (secondary, primary..) using the audit configuration in the SQL Compliance Manager management console.

data.name: label48.Text
data.value: Note: Adding privileged users can only be done if you have permission to list server roles and logins. If the SQL Server is in a non-trusted domain, you will not be able to add privileged users until the SQLcompliance agent is deployed and the server registration is complete.
